Easiest way to use LaTeX (math typesetting): 

download LyX

type code: LyX > New Document > Insert > TeX code
(example:
\begin{equation}
\label{bla}
1+1=2
\end{equation}
In equation \ref{bla} we revisit arithmetic.)

add preamble: Document > Settings > LaTeX Preamble
(example:
try viewing document with and without \usepackage{hyperref} in the preamble)

view: Update, View

other: click-and-go, just like word processor



Use Asymptote (math drawing):

download from https://asymptote.sourceforge.io/
useful reference: https://asymptote.sourceforge.io/doc/Index.html

interactive mode:
$asy
example: $draw((0,0)--(100,100));
$exit

actual use:
open any text editor
type code
(example:
settings.outformat="png";
or 
settings.outformat="pdf";
or 
none of the above
label("Hello world!");)
save as test.asy
$asy test.asy
open test.png or test.pdf or test.eps

lots of examples in asymptote directory > examples
